import os
import pandas as pd

data_folder = "../data"

df_list = []

for media in ["abc"]:
    media_folder = os.path.join(data_folder, media)
    
    for file_name in os.listdir(media_folder):
        if file_name.endswith(".csv"):
            file_path = os.path.join(media_folder, file_name)
            
            year = int(file_name.replace(media, "").replace(".csv", ""))  
            
            temp_df = pd.read_csv(file_path)
            
            temp_df["Media"] = media
            temp_df["Year"] = year
            
            df_list.append(temp_df)

df = pd.concat(df_list, ignore_index=True)

print(df.head())
print(df.info())

wordcloud¶

In [ ]:
from wordcloud import WordCloud
from collections import Counter
import re

text = " ".join(df['headline_from_url'].dropna().astype(str))
text = re.sub(r'[^a-zA-Z ]', '', text.lower())
word_freq = Counter(text.split())

wordcloud = WordCloud(width=800, height=400, background_color='white').generate_from_frequencies(word_freq)

plt.figure(figsize=(10, 5))
plt.imshow(wordcloud, interpolation="bilinear")
plt.axis("off")
plt.title("Word Cloud of ABC News Headlines")
plt.show()

# word frequency
vectorizer = CountVectorizer(stop_words='english', max_features=100)
X = vectorizer.fit_transform(df['cleaned_headline'])
word_freq = np.asarray(X.sum(axis=0)).flatten()
words = vectorizer.get_feature_names_out()

word_freq_df = pd.DataFrame({'Word': words, 'Frequency': word_freq})
word_freq_df = word_freq_df.sort_values(by='Frequency', ascending=False)

headline sentiment score¶

In [ ]:
from nltk.sentiment.vader import SentimentIntensityAnalyzer
import numpy as np
import pandas as pd

# initialize VADER sentiment analyzer
sia = SentimentIntensityAnalyzer()

#  cleaned_headline sentiment score
df['Sentiment'] = df['cleaned_headline'].apply(lambda x: sia.polarity_scores(x)['compound'])

plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
sns.histplot(df['Sentiment'], bins=30, kde=True, color="skyblue")
plt.title("Sentiment Score Distribution for Headlines in ABC News")
plt.xlabel("Sentiment Score")
plt.ylabel("Frequency")
plt.show()

words sentiment¶

In [ ]:
from collections import defaultdict

# words sentiment
word_sentiment = defaultdict(list)

# Calculate the sentiment score for each word in the title of each news item

for headline, sentiment in zip(df['cleaned_headline'], df['Sentiment']):
    words = headline.split()
    for word in words:
        word_sentiment[word].append(sentiment)

# Calculate the average sentiment score for each word

word_avg_sentiment = {word: np.mean(scores) for word, scores in word_sentiment.items()}

word_sentiment_df = pd.DataFrame(list(word_avg_sentiment.items()), columns=['Word', 'Avg_Sentiment'])
word_sentiment_df = word_sentiment_df.sort_values(by='Avg_Sentiment', ascending=False)

# top 20
print(word_sentiment_df.head(20))

# categorize
word_sentiment_df['Sentiment_Category'] = pd.cut(word_sentiment_df['Avg_Sentiment'],
